sment. The returns are translated into English and a glossary has been added to explain how Latin terms have been translated.There is also a translation of the collection of a fifteenth for Shillington in 1301.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aTaxationvListszEnglandzBedfordshire. 4aModern History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aBarford hundred.  aBedford.  aBiggleswade hundred.  aDunstable.  aFlitt hundred.  aLeighton Buzzard.  aLuton.  aShillington.  ataxation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781800107274?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781800107274423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781800107274/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles